Key Match Events: The Cubs rallied from an early deficit to tie the score but couldn’t quite pull off a series sweep.
Cody Bellinger hit a home run during the fifth inning.
Ian Happ and Dansby Swanson also scored during the fifth inning.
The Cubs made two mistakes on the bases which contributed to their 10-8 loss.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Craig Counsell commented that the team played two excellent games on the bases and on defense, but made two mistakes on the bases in the final game which contributed to the loss.
